        <updateDate>2023-06-01T22:36:30Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>No Oil Producing and Exporting Cartels Act of 2023 or NOPEC </b></p> <p>This bill prohibits a foreign state from engaging in collective action impacting the market, supply, price, or distribution of oil, natural gas, or any other petroleum product in the U.S. Specifically, a foreign state is prohibited from</p> <ul> <li>collective action that limits the production or distribution of such product, </li> <li>collective action to set or maintain the price of such product, or </li> <li>any other action that restrains trade of such product. </li> </ul> <p>Specified defenses such as sovereign immunity (i.e., a foreign state's immunity from the jurisdiction of U.S. courts) and the act of state doctrine (i.e., the prohibition of a court invalidating an official act of a foreign sovereign performed within its own territory) shall not apply to a foreign state's violation of this bill.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
